channel.title: Socks proxy with Java on web browser
channel.description:
I have made a shh tunnel and configured firefox to use socks proxy 127.0.0.1:1080. The internet works, but Java doesn't. I have gone to the Java control panel and changed the proxy settings to 127.0.0.1:1080. I receive this error when I try going to an applet on a browser [CODE]basic: Added progress listener: sun.plugin.util.ProgressMonitorAdapter@22f558 basic: Added progress listener: sun.plugin.util.ProgressMonitorAdapter@1826b5c basic: Added progress listener: sun.plugin.util.ProgressMonitorAdapter@1857eeb basic: Plugin2ClassLoader.addURL parent called for http://www.java.com/applet/TestVM2-test.jar network: Cache entry not found [url: http://www.bodo.com/Applets/SineText/, version: null] network: Cache entry not found [url: http://www.bodo.com/Applets/SineText/SineText.class, version: null] network: Connecting http://www.bodo.com/Applets/SineText/SineText.class with proxy=SOCKS @ novirusthanks.org/127.0.0.1:1080 network: Cache entry not found [url: http://www.java.com/applet/TestVM2-test.jar, version: null] network: Connecting http://www.java.com/applet/TestVM2-test.jar with proxy=SOCKS @ novirusthanks.org/127.0.0.1:1080 network: Cache entry not found [url: http://javatester.org/, version: null] network: Cache entry not found [url: http://javatester.org/JavaVersionDisplayApplet.class, version: null] network: Connecting http://javatester.org/JavaVersionDisplayApplet.class with proxy=SOCKS @ novirusthanks.org/127.0.0.1:1080 network: Connection http://www.bodo.com/Applets/SineText/SineText.class, novirusthanks.org/127.0.0.1:1080java.net.SocketException: Malformed reply from SOCKS server failed: removed from proxy cache network: Connecting http://www.bodo.com:80/ with proxy=SOCKS @ novirusthanks.org/127.0.0.1:1080 network: Connection http://javatester.org/JavaVersionDisplayApplet.class, novirusthanks.org/127.0.0.1:1080java.net.SocketException: Malformed reply from SOCKS server failed: removed from proxy cache network: Connecting http://javatester.org:80/ with proxy=SOCKS @ novirusthanks.org/127.0.0.1:1080[/CODE]
anybody have a solution?

item.dc:creator: @CoonHunter CoonHunter
item.description:
@CoonHunter wrote:

Check the page source and make sure it is getting to the browser’s source. If all is well there, the ssh tunnel might be filtering that out.

Kidpaparoach:

I felt so dumb reading this post… Cache entry not found da problummmmm

Most likely not the issue. I think its looking for a cache entry for pre-downloaded data to save SOME bandwidth.
